            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar <lb n="2"/>divi Nervae <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>Nerva Traianus <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Germ</abbr><ex>anicus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Dacic</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/>XIII <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> VI co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> V <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/>viam et pontes <lb n="9"/>a Benevento Brundisium <lb n="10"/>pecunia sua fecit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Es handelt sich um 2 Tafeln mit der gleichen Inschrift, die an derselben Stelle gefunden wurden. Maße der anderen Tafel: 130 x 90 x 30; I-Feld: 89,5 x 61; B-Höhe: 6-3. Y: 10.12.108 - 9.12.109.</p>
            </div>
